-Burnt-out Tired Cookies:
-Base Ingredients
185 g all-purpose flour
25 g dark brown sugar
200 g granulated sugar
8 tbsp unsalted butter
-Flavor Ingredients
0.5 tsp ginger
50 g fig
---
Instructions
Step 1: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F.
Step 2: Mix together dry ingredients, combining the following in a large bowl: flour, ginger. In another bowl, cream together the following: dark brown sugar, granulated sugar, unsalted butter, .
Step 3: Gradually add the dry ingredients to the wet ingredients, mixing well. Once mixed, add the fig.
Step 4: Let the mixture rest for 9 hours in the refrigerator. On a baking sheet lined with parchment paper, add 50 grams of dough, rolled into a sphere. Bake for 12 minutes, turning the sheet around halfway through the baking time.
Step 5: Let the cookies cool.